values:
I seriously hate men sometimes.&nbsp; Nothing in the world makes me more crazy than having a man in my life.&nbsp;&nbsp; 

I've been involved with someone for two months now, and it's been fantastic.&nbsp; I have a knack for attracting commitment-phobe men who either don't pay any attention to me or who just couldn't care less if I was in their life&nbsp;or not.&nbsp; Suddenly here is this&nbsp;amazing guy that's&nbsp;talking to me for hours on the phone every day; texting me&nbsp;every night to say good night, every morning to tell me I'm beautiful and that he's thinking of me; exchaning&nbsp;long, wonderful emails with me where&nbsp;we tell each other absolutely everything...he paid me&nbsp;almost constant attention (without being creepy, mind you).&nbsp; I loved it.&nbsp; It has seriously been 10 long&nbsp;years since&nbsp;I've&nbsp;been with someone that has made me feel as good as this guy does.&nbsp;&nbsp; 

Suddenly it's not the same anymore.&nbsp; I&nbsp;still get texts, but they aren't quite as&nbsp;sweet nor as frequent.&nbsp; Our phone calls are shorter, are emails are fewer between...in fact, today was the first day in&nbsp;two days months that I&nbsp;didn't receive a single&nbsp;email from him.&nbsp;&nbsp;And I'm hurt.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;He's still saying all the right things, and doing all the right things...yet I can't help feeling mopey and a bit neglected by the lack of attention.&nbsp; I will admit, I'm an insecure person, as much as I try not to be.&nbsp; I'm very easily offended by this sort of thing.&nbsp; I try really hard not to be...but I feel that I truly can't help it.&nbsp;&nbsp; I'm also extremely anxious--combine that with my overactive imagination and you have an instant panic attack.&nbsp; 

Is this common?&nbsp; Do you reach a certain comfort level with someone that they finally decide they don't NEED to email you or text you every day?&nbsp; The newness is gone, you're 'caught'...now they don't need to make an effort?&nbsp; I'm not sure what to think, especially since I haven't had what you would call a normal relationship in years.&nbsp;&nbsp; 

My anxiety issues make me very high maintenance...and I'm struggling not to freak out about this.&nbsp; I'm hoping this is a phase, or a fluke, or just a part of a relationship where two people are growing more comfortable with each other.&nbsp; Or does this mean he's losing interest...?
